        {
            "title": "BTC, ETH, XRP, and Dogecoin prices dip on Christmas Day, BTC at $87,267.64. Thin trading volume with $138M liquidated in 24 hours.$crypto",
            "id": "569fbf03-daab-4ea1-906a-f94c2129d4e5",
            "description": "On Christmas Day, leading cryptocurrencies saw stagnant prices with Bitcoin at $87,267.64 (-0.43%), Ethereum at $2,916.07 (-0.91%), XRP at $1.83 (-1.15%), Solana at $120.58 (-1.51%), and Dogecoin at $0.1240 (-3.25%). Bitcoin peaked near $88,500 but dropped below $87,000, as trading volume decreased by 14% in 24 hours. Ethereum struggled to surpass $3,000 and retreated to the mid-$2,900 range. The market saw over $138 million liquidated, mostly in long positions. Bitcoin's open interest fell by 0.94% as short positions surpassed longs, signaling \"Extreme Fear\" sentiment. Full details on Benzinga.com.",
